The Chairman of Apapa Local Government Area in Lagos State Idowu Sebanjo has presented cash and gifts to the woman that delivered the first Baby-of-the-Year in the council. Mrs Sukurat Okunade was delivered of a baby boy at Ijora Oloye Primary Health Centre (PHC), by 12.:01 am on January 1. Sebanjo described the baby as a sign of blessing to the council. According to her, the mother is a lucky woman.   AbdulRazaq attributes success in health care to committed…     Ogun to introduce ‘water kiosking’     Lagos APC chair hails Faleke for lifting constituents   “I pray that she nurtures the child well. Children are blessings from God and every child has a purpose and mission on earth. I pray that the parents will look after the child with love and care so that the blessings of the Lord will radiate on the family,” she said. - Advertisement - The council chief promised to improve the quality of the schools to meet the best standard, to enable pupils learn in a conducive atmosphere. Sebanjo said the council would also upgrade the primary healthcare centre. Mrs Okunade ,while thanking God for the safe delivery, appreciated the council boss for the gifts and cash. Some officials that accompanied Sebanjo to the health centre include Vice Chairman Ganiu Ismail;  and Medical Officer of Health Dr Oludolapo Sotunde.